Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Though 9 out of 42 patients randomised were excluded, the reasons for the same are stated and they do not differ substantially between the groups, thus indicating that the results might not be biased.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Being an objective outcome, it is unlikely that assessment of the outcome would be influenced by knowledge of allocation group
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Trial analysed as per a priori registered protocol.
